<node id="&quot;INSURED AUTO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A vehicle covered under the policy, for which the medical payments limit applies."&lt;SEP&gt;"A vehicle covered under the policy, which may be used for hire or to carry persons or property for a charge, triggering the D O C 1 exclusion."&lt;SEP&gt;"A vehicle covered under the policy, with liability limits applied individually per vehicle."&lt;SEP&gt;"A vehicle that is covered under the insurance policy, which may be temporarily replaced by a substitute auto during service, repair, theft, or destruction."&lt;SEP&gt;"An auto covered under the policy and being operated by someone in an automobile business."&lt;SEP&gt;"An auto to which a trailer is attached, and which is insured."&lt;SEP&gt;"An automobile covered under the policy, including private passenger or utility autos, for which the insured is protected from liability."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is a motor vehicle covered under the policy, and permission from the policyholder is required for someone to be considered an insured person while using it."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is a motor vehicle covered under the policy, including those described in the declarations, acquired during the policy period, temporarily used, or operated with permission."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is a motor vehicle described in the Policy Declarations or a vehicle used to replace a previously insured vehicle."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is a vehicle covered under the policy, including replacements, additional autos, substitutes, non-owned autos, trailers, and camper units under specific conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is a vehicle covered under the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is a vehicle described in the policy and covered under the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is a vehicle that the trailer is attached to."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is covered for direct and accidental loss from collision."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is covered for loss not caused by collision."&lt;SEP&gt;"An insured auto is involved in a collision with another auto insured by Allstate."&lt;SEP&gt;"An underinsured motor vehicle is not considered an insured auto under this coverage."&lt;SEP&gt;"The auto being transported, covered under collision or comprehensive insurance."&lt;SEP&gt;"The auto described in the policy, where clothing and luggage are located."&lt;SEP&gt;"The auto described in the policy, where tapes or similar items are located at the time of loss."&lt;SEP&gt;"The insured auto is the vehicle covered under the policy, within which the Sound System is located."&lt;SEP&gt;"The vehicle to which the trailer is attached, which must be a private passenger auto or utility auto, and is covered under the policy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9464bb7af811d8f15562644a4b28627a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9177db9bf28d1b94e41d2945af46c2ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b1a9c0ee5abff30de9434ff54575a1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de9df743c1a11a8ab7dd8d3778fbd139&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a3c5316326203ee0a115e648929c62e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a1058b402f07e43095cfbfe1691d379&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb067276caaf4fa58c030146cde3e6e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b55b5dbebd0735cd54f0def3352978c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6215ed56b5c8c7128976e54f6afde15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8be2695f13a2055df9eb3b1f448e01ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e112c7cb29439b72e7ec24cc60020e88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccb8c813f593e1d6b773fb60656c296b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82005be4122ff546dea4915156b29767</data>
