<node id="&quot;ARBITRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A dispute resolution method that may be used for claims over $3000, but only with mutual agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"A method of dispute resolution where a neutral third party makes a binding decision if an agreement cannot be reached."&lt;SEP&gt;"A method of resolving disputes outside of court, used when the claim amount is $3000 or less."&lt;SEP&gt;"Arbitration is a method used to decide benefits and amounts payable when an agreement cannot be reached between the insured person and Allstate."&lt;SEP&gt;"Arbitration is a method used to resolve disputes when an agreement cannot be reached between the insured person and Allstate."&lt;SEP&gt;"Arbitration is pending in the county of jurisdiction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9464bb7af811d8f15562644a4b28627a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de3dee890ed2c9f37d79ceb62462bb87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e94c444615403bb65cb8316d74e2ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a1058b402f07e43095cfbfe1691d379</data>
</node>
