<node id="&quot;COVERAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A policy provision applicable to the loss that must be in place for reimbursement."&lt;SEP&gt;"A type of insurance protection that does not apply to certain situations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage applies only when a premium for it is shown on the Policy Declarations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage can be broadened during the policy period."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage continues until the end of the policy period after the policyholder's death."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage refers to the insurance protection provided under the policy, which excludes certain death scenarios."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage refers to the insurance protection provided under the policy, which may result in payment to a person."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage refers to the protection provided by the insurance policy for specific risks, such as auto accidents, medical payments, or death indemnity, and applies only when a premium is shown."&lt;SEP&gt;"The coverage for the involved or chosen auto does not include limits from other autos."&lt;SEP&gt;"The coverage in question does not apply to disabilities sustained in the course of certain occupations, particularly those involving vehicles."</data>
