<node id="&quot;FOUR WHEEL PRIVATE PASSENGER AUTO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A four wheel private passenger auto is a land motor vehicle designed for use on public roads, used for personal transportation, and not for commercial purposes. It is covered under the policy if all other private passenger autos or utility autos owned by the policyholder are insured, provided the policyholder notifies Allstate within 60 days of acquisition and pays any additional premium."&lt;SEP&gt;"A four wheel private passenger auto is a vehicle designed for personal use on public roads, covered under the policy if described in the declarations or replaced within 60 days."&lt;SEP&gt;"A four-wheel private passenger auto is a vehicle covered under the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"A type of auto covered under the policy, including replacement vehicles."&lt;SEP&gt;"A type of automobile used for personal transportation, covered under the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"A vehicle used for personal transportation, covered under the policy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9177db9bf28d1b94e41d2945af46c2ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a3c5316326203ee0a115e648929c62e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb067276caaf4fa58c030146cde3e6e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6215ed56b5c8c7128976e54f6afde15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82005be4122ff546dea4915156b29767</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EACH PERSON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"POLICY_LIMIT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The limit for each person is a separate cap on the amount payable per individual injured in an accident."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount Allstate will pay for bodily injury to one person in a single accident."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-810b812ea27a9a4ae98ffeee6a14930d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e59deb97f8984555fae3eed52c917fe</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESIDENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A person living in the same household as the policyholder, who is an insured person."&lt;SEP&gt;"A person who lives in a household with the intent to continue residing there."&lt;SEP&gt;"A person who lives in the policyholder's household with the intent to continue residing there. This includes unmarried dependent children who are temporarily away but plan to return."&lt;SEP&gt;"A person who physically resides in a household with the intention of continuing residence."&lt;SEP&gt;"A resident is a person who lives in the household with the intention of continuing residence."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-810b812ea27a9a4ae98ffeee6a14930d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb067276caaf4fa58c030146cde3e6e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6215ed56b5c8c7128976e54f6afde15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccb8c813f593e1d6b773fb60656c296b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82005be4122ff546dea4915156b29767</data>
</node>
