  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"An auto that does not have liability insurance, and whose owner or operator may be responsible for bodily injury to an insured person."&lt;SEP&gt;"An uninsured auto is a motor vehicle with no bodily injury liability bond or insurance policy in effect at the time of the accident."&lt;SEP&gt;"An uninsured auto is a motor vehicle without valid liability coverage, including those with denied coverage, insolvent insurers, underinsured vehicles, or hit-and-run vehicles."&lt;SEP&gt;"An uninsured auto is a vehicle involved in an accident that lacks liability insurance."</data>
