  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A replacement vehicle covered under the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"A substitute auto is a vehicle temporarily used when the insured auto is being serviced, repaired, stolen, or destroyed, and is not owned by the policyholder or a resident."&lt;SEP&gt;"A substitute auto is a vehicle used in place of the insured auto, and coverage applies only after all other collectible auto medical insurance is exhausted."&lt;SEP&gt;"A substitute auto is temporarily used when the insured auto is unavailable."&lt;SEP&gt;"A temporary replacement vehicle not owned by the policyholder or a resident, used while the insured auto is being serviced, repaired, or has been stolen or destroyed. It must be a four wheel private passenger auto or utility auto."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-442e0db5ed8682bcab7a54824da0d7b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a3c5316326203ee0a115e648929c62e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb067276caaf4fa58c030146cde3e6e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82005be4122ff546dea4915156b29767&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12ffe8b6b2ba410a0c8e955ca34e8cfb</data>
